-- India cbank not considering opening up ECB route in a big way - deputy governor
-- By Suvashree Dey Choudhury and Himank Sharma
-- Wed Oct 08, 2014 08:29AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, Oct 8 (Reuters) - The Reserve Bank of India is not considering further opening up the external commercial borrowing (ECB) route, Deputy Governor H.R. Khan told reporters on the sidelines of a conference on Wednesday.

Last month, the central bank had allowed foreign lenders to issue rupee-denominated loans to Indian companies overseas. [ID:nI8N0N801O] Khan also reiterated the RBI is working on allowing settlements of government bonds in the Euroclear system, the world's biggest securities settlement system. [ID:nI8N0NO007]